      <div class="msgContentFrame">An excellent point Jay. There is a sort of silent etiquette when it comes to multiple mages in a party. At the moment I am finding it a bit of a race to get the cures off first. With a little bit of collaboration we can all get max sp this way. I don't agree with one person spamming PD/SD because it means that that mage is not getting as many sp as the others in the party.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179">Loadstone Profile</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649">Thaumaturge Guide</a> <br /> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1229110.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
