      <div class="msgContentFrame">I have started to run daily parties in my LinkShell Disciples of Eorzea in Fabul, we normally run parties of 6-10 players daily sometimes 2 parties for about a week now, ive found myself sometimes with 5-6 mages in 1 party, fighting mobs that can do from 300 damage all the way to 1k on the tank(not a GLAD) even i end up tanking the adds sometimes luckily been hit for 700-800 tops, in these situations all our mages have Tier 2 spells, we designate 1 person as healer and the rest as backup, we all heal the first 20-30% of the mobs HP, and as soon as we get atleast 200SP those mages switch to damage and designated mage keeps healing, and only when tanks HP falls to a % where healing help is needed, we do so. <br /> <br />Dont be confused by damage spells SP, one good pro/br damage hit can net you 300 SP in 1 hit, personally had a 290sp hit last night in a 11 players parrty even tho ive had fatigue for 5 days now. <br /> <br />It works well but these are players that are starting to get used to party with each other, they are getting used to knowing how each other likes to play, so it makes it alot easier to play in parties, its a good advice from any player to try and find yourself a party as static as posible, as to minimize ppl messing up.Good luck. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Oct 27th 2010  6:03pm by AggroDoctor </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4127062" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=4127062">Aggro Doctor's Rap Sheet</a> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1815324.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
