      <div class="msgContentFrame">I been in a sort of static party for a couple of weeks now and I can't stress how much better they are. Unfortunately a couple of our members have been leveling with other parties and are now way higher than me so that has come to an end. I did a pick up party last night and it wasnt going very well still by the time I had to go. A good bunch of players that know each other well probably nets about 2k or more per hour than the average pick up. Although I have also been in some fantastic pickups, a static is a great way to go if you can.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179">Loadstone Profile</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649">Thaumaturge Guide</a> <br /> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1229110.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
