      <div class="msgContentFrame">Yeah, there's a pretty good case for Cure 1 spam in a large party setting.  Efficiency and sharing the SP is only part of it though, as I think that healing enmity scales different in XIV then it does in XI (I rip aggro with Cure 2 / Sacrifice 2 regularly if I'm forced to cast them) <br /> <br />If you are in a large party setting though with multiple healers fighting over the healing SP, there is a TON of SP to be had from debuffs.  Once you get Siphon MP in your rotation @ level 20, your MP pool pretty much becomes a non-issue, and you can spam cast debuffs for nice SP gains.   <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>MUTED</div></div>
